**Code Explanation:**

The code implements the training pipeline for the Super-Resolution Denoising Autoencoder (SR-DAE) using a composite loss function and a curriculum learning strategy. 1. Data Pipeline: The CompSepDataset class is updated to accept valid_indices, allowing us to filter the dataset for curriculum learning. It dynamically samples SO and Planck noise, applies random noise scaling, and performs spatial augmentations (rotations and flips) to improve rotational invariance. The inputs are normalized using the global statistics computed in Step 1. 2. Composite Loss: The CompositeLoss module combines three terms: L1 Loss (L_L1): Pixel-wise absolute error between the reconstructed tSZ map and the ground truth. Feature Matching Loss (L_FeatureMatching): Computes the L1 difference of the spatial gradients (extracted via Sobel filters) to encourage the model to preserve sharp edges and structural details. Spectral Loss (L_Spectral): Computes the Mean Squared Error (MSE) between the radial power spectra of the prediction and the target. The code attempts to use utils.powers directly on PyTorch tensors. If utils.powers relies on NumPy (which breaks the computation graph and prevents backpropagation), it gracefully falls back to a custom, fully differentiable PyTorch implementation of the 2D radial power spectrum. To maintain efficiency, this term is only computed on a subset of the batch every 10 iterations. 3. Curriculum Learning: The training is divided into two stages. Stage 1 (first 30% of epochs) trains exclusively on high-intensity patches (where the maximum tSZ value exceeds the 75th percentile) to help the model establish the fundamental mapping for high-mass clusters. Stage 2 trains on the full dataset to refine the recovery of subtle, diffuse gas signatures. 4. Training Loop: The model is trained using the AdamW optimizer and a OneCycleLR scheduler. Mixed-precision training (FP16) via torch.cuda.amp is employed to optimize memory usage and compute speed on the RTX PRO 6000 GPU. The trained model weights and loss history are saved to the data/ directory.

**Modifications:**

Added curriculum learning logic, implemented composite loss with spectral consistency, integrated mixed-precision training, and ensured all file paths point to the data/ directory.

