**Code Explanation:**

This script performs the CIB-tSZ null test and scientific validation of the trained SR-DAE model. 1. Inference Pipeline: It loads the trained model and runs inference on all 1523 patches. To ensure deterministic evaluation, it uses fixed noise realizations (i_so=0, i_planck=0). The InferenceDataset class handles the data loading and un-normalization. 2. CIB-tSZ Null Test: It creates a control dataset by shuffling the CIB patch indices (353, 545, 857 GHz) relative to the tSZ ground truth and low-frequency channels. This isolates the effect of spatial correlation between CIB and tSZ. If the model relies on physical gas pressure rather than just "painting" CIB morphology, the reconstruction performance should degrade significantly on this null set. 3. Cross-Correlation (r_ell): It computes the global cross-correlation coefficient r_ell between the reconstructed maps and the ground truth using the utils.powers function. This metric quantifies the scale-dependent reconstruction fidelity. 4. Y_SZ-M Relation and Scatter: It extracts the Y_SZ-M relation by using the patch-integrated ground truth tSZ signal as a proxy for cluster mass. It then calculates the residual scatter (standard deviation of residuals) as a function of mass for the standard reconstruction, the null test reconstruction, and the raw SO-LAT 150 GHz data (converted to Compton-y units). 5. Saving Metrics: All computed metrics and a subset of the reconstructed maps are saved to disk for subsequent visualization and analysis. Key quantitative results are printed to the console.

